President Donald J. Trump will be meeting with the leaders of The Bahamas, the Dominican Republic, Haiti, Jamaica, and Saint Lucia on March 22, 2019. The purpose of the meeting is to reaffirm the strong friendship and commitment between the United States and these Caribbean countries, and to highlight the importance of the Caribbean in the hemisphere. President Trump will discuss his vision for the relationships with these countries, including potential opportunities for energy investment. Additionally, the President will address the need for security cooperation and counter China's predatory economic practices in the region. He will also express gratitude for these countries' support for peace and democracy in Venezuela. The United States aims to continue being a reliable partner for the Caribbean.